                      Talent
                    















                    Working for our Company
                  



                            How many employees does The Estée Lauder Companies have?
                          





At June 30, 2016, we had approximately 46,000 full-time employees worldwide (including demonstrators at points of sale who are employed by us).






                            How can I work for your Company?
                          





You may view and apply for positions within our global corporate offices and field locations here. Representatives in our stores are hired by the stores in which they work.






                            Can I apply to more than one job?
                          





Candidates are welcome to apply to any open opportunities of interest that fit their skills and experiences. Please note that candidates will only be considered and interviewed for one position at a time.






                            Do you sponsor work visas?
                          





For those candidates requiring work authorization, we will consider on a case-by-case basis sponsoring visas for candidates who are offered a role at or above the Director level.






                            What can I expect from the interview process?
                          





Our interview process is an opportunity for us to better understand your capabilities, experiences and career ambitions as well as assess cultural fit. Candidates who successfully match the profile of what we’re looking for in the role will be invited to interview, either by phone or in person. Interviews are conducted by Human Resources, Hiring Managers and Leaders. Our interview style consists of behavioral interviews that assess core competencies and cultural fit.






                            How can I be informed of new openings in my area of interest?
                          





We encourage candidates to create a personal profile on The Estée Lauder Companies job sites. Within that profile, you are able to designate the areas of interest or specific functions where you would be interested in working. When new roles become available that match your preferences, our job posting system will automatically notify you.




                    Investing in our Company
                  



                            Who owns The Estée Lauder Companies?
                          





The Estée Lauder Companies is a publicly-traded, family controlled company.






                            What is the stock symbol for The Estée Lauder Companies Inc. Class A Common Stock and what stock exchange is the Company listed on?
                          





The stock symbol is EL and it is listed on the New York Stock Exchange.






                            When was The Estée Lauder Companies’ initial public offering and at what price did it go public?
                          





The Company went public on November 16, 1995 at a price of $26 per share (equal to $6.50 adjusted for stock splits).






                            What are The Estée Lauder Companies’ earnings release dates for the coming year?
                          





Earnings release and conference call dates can be found in the Events & Presentations  section on this site. Additionally, archives of past earnings conference calls can also be accessed.






                            When is the next Annual Meeting of Stockholders?
                          





This information and more can be found on the Events & Presentations section on this site.




                    About our Products
                  



                            How can I find out the ingredients of a product?
                          





The ingredients in all of our products can be found on the packaging. If you are unable to find the ingredient listing for your product, contact us with the exact name and shade of the product you use or would be interested in using and we will send you the ingredient listing.






                            How can I find a product that has been discontinued?
                          





 If you are a consumer in North America, please visit our Gone But Not Forgotten page. For all other regions, contact us.






                            Why was my product discontinued?
                          





Please know that the decision to discontinue a product is rarely an easy one, and the matter is always given significant thought and consideration, including analysis of purchasing patterns and also the latest technological advances.






                            Do your products contain parabens?
                          





Read about our company's stance on Ingredients.






                            Do your products contain microbeads?
                          





Read about our company's stance on Microbeads.






                            Are your products tested on animals?
                          





Read about our company's stance on Animal Testing.




















