IT Budget




Estee Lauder Companies, Inc. is a manufacturer, marketer and distributor of skin care, makeup, fragrance, and hair care products primarily under Estee Lauder, Aramis, Clinique, Prescriptives, Lab Series, Origins, American Beauty, Aveda, and Good Skin brand names worldwide.

It is also… MoreEstee Lauder Companies, Inc. is a manufacturer, marketer and distributor of skin care, makeup, fragrance, and hair care products primarily under Estee Lauder, Aramis, Clinique, Prescriptives, Lab Series, Origins, American Beauty, Aveda, and Good Skin brand names worldwide.

It is also the global licensee for fragrances and cosmetics sold under the Tommy Hilfiger, Donna Karan, Michael Kors, Donald Trump, Sean John, Missoni and Daisy Fuentes brand names.
Estee Lauder Companies, Inc. is a manufacturer, marketer and distributor of skin care, makeup, fragrance, and hair care products primarily under Estee Lauder, Aramis, Clinique, Prescriptives, Lab Series, Origins, American Beauty, Aveda, and Good Skin brand names worldwide.

It is also… MoreEstee Lauder Companies, Inc. is a manufacturer, marketer and distributor of skin care, makeup, fragrance, and hair care products primarily under Estee Lauder, Aramis, Clinique, Prescriptives, Lab Series, Origins, American Beauty, Aveda, and Good Skin brand names worldwide.

It is also the global licensee for fragrances and cosmetics sold under the Tommy Hilfiger, Donna Karan, Michael Kors, Donald Trump, Sean John, Missoni and Daisy Fuentes brand names.

IT Structure
•Estee Lauder's IT department is based in New York, NY. 
•The majority of the company's IT staff reside at this location, as well as at a location in Melville, NY.
•ELC Online, a division of Estee Lauder, utilizes the same IT team and resources. 
•All US Desktop support and Help Desk services are located in Melville, NY. 

IT Vendors
In June 2009, Estee Lauder signed a deal with Computer Sciences Corporation to outsource some IT functions including network administration. 

IT Snippets
 2013:
• engaged in BI initiatives with global brands.

2012:
• Windows 7 rollout 
• Increase spending on data management and network security as it implements a BYOD program.
• Increase spending on SAP and network solutions in order to meet the corporate requirements for a standardized global network.





